static font

Variable font must have a STAT table.

Libre Franklin Thin Regular (LibreFranklin-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin Thin'.

Libre Franklin Thin Italic (LibreFranklin-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. Libre Franklin Thin Italic (LibreFranklin-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Libre Franklin Light Regular (LibreFranklin-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin Light'.

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Libre Franklin Light Italic (LibreFranklin-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Libre Franklin Regular (LibreFranklin-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

'space' in NID 6 cause issues in fontbook for Mac.

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-Regular', Everything looks good.

Libre Franklin Medium Regular (LibreFranklin-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin Medium'.

Pass

Libre Franklin Medium Italic (LibreFranklin-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Libre Franklin Medium Italic (LibreFranklin-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Libre Franklin SemiBold Italic (LibreFranklin-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Libre Franklin Bold (LibreFranklin-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. MS NID 6

, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Libre Franklin ExtraBold Regular (LibreFranklin-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin ExtraBold'.

Libre Franklin ExtraBold Italic (LibreFranklin-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Libre Franklin Black Regular (LibreFranklin-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LibreFranklin-Black', Everything looks good.

Pass

, most common Monotype license test is:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Libre Franklin Black Regular (LibreFranklin-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Libre Franklin' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Libre Franklin Black'.

Pass
